        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 2 at 5:43PM CDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 543 PM CDT/443 PM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of
strong thunderstorms 9 miles south of Paxton, or 22 miles southeast
of Ogallala, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sutherland, Sutherland Reservoir State Recreation Area, and
O'Fallons.

This includes Interstate 80 in Nebraska between mile markers 151 and
163.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM
CDT/midnight MDT/ for southwestern Nebraska.</instruction>
